{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_0","type":"agent_message","text":"final_filename: p21.cir\n\nObjective: Create a SPICE netlist for a single-stage telescopic cascode opamp using VDD = 5 V. The circuit must expose input nodes Vinp, Vinn, Vbias1, Vbias2, Vbias3, Vbias4 and output nodes Voutp, Vout. The required verification is a DC operating point analysis with `.op`.\n\nTopology: Use a fully differential NMOS-input telescopic cascode structure with one NMOS tail current source, two NMOS input devices, two NMOS cascode devices above the input pair, two PMOS current-source load devices, and two PMOS cascode load devices. This satisfies the “4 NMOS as cascode input pair, 4 PMOS as cascode loads, and 1 tail current” intent while preserving two high-impedance output nodes.\n\nRequired devices:\n- M1: NMOS input transistor for Vinp branch.\n- M2: NMOS input transistor for Vinn branch.\n- M5: NMOS tail current source.\n- M6, M7: NMOS cascode devices above M1/M2.\n- M3, M4: PMOS upper current-source load devices.\n- M8, M9: PMOS cascode load devices below M3/M4.\n- VDD source from VDD to 0 at 5 V.\n- Independent DC sources for every named input node: Vinp, Vinn, Vbias1, Vbias2, Vbias3, Vbias4.\n\nKey interconnectivity:\n- M5 drain connects to tail node, source and bulk to 0, gate to Vbias1.\n- M1 source connects to tail node, drain connects to internal node nleft, gate to Vinp, bulk to tail node.\n- M2 source connects to tail node, drain connects to internal node nright, gate to Vinn, bulk to tail node.\n- M6 source connects to nleft, drain connects to Voutp, gate to Vbias2, bulk to nleft.\n- M7 source connects to nright, drain connects to Vout, gate to Vbias2, bulk to nright.\n- PMOS load stack on Voutp side: M3 source and bulk to VDD, drain to pleft, gate to Vbias4; M8 source and bulk to pleft, drain to Voutp, gate to Vbias3.\n- PMOS load stack on Vout side: M4 source and bulk to VDD, drain to pright, gate to Vbias4; M9 source and bulk to pright, drain to Vout, gate to Vbias3.\n- Voutp and Vout are the high-impedance differential output nodes between the NMOS cascodes and PMOS cascodes.\n\nBiasing assumptions:\n- Use VDD = 5 V.\n- Vinp = 2.5 V DC and Vinn = 2.5 V DC for balanced operating point.\n- Use threshold-aware single-supply biasing so every MOSFET conducts at `.op`.\n- Suggested explicit DC biases:\n  - Vbias1 = 1.2 V for the NMOS tail source gate, giving roughly 0.5 V overdrive.\n  - Vbias2 = 3.0 V for NMOS cascode gates, keeping NMOS input drains above saturation while allowing output headroom.\n  - Vbias3 = 2.0 V for PMOS cascode gates, biasing the PMOS cascodes on while placing output nodes near mid-supply.\n  - Vbias4 = 4.0 V for PMOS upper current-source gates, giving roughly 0.3 V PMOS overdrive from VDD.\n- MOS bulk connections should be tied to each device source as required by the task guidance.\n- Use the provided nominal MOS model sizing:\n  - NMOS: Vth = 0.7 V, kp = 100u, W = 50u, L = 1u.\n  - PMOS: Vth = -0.7 V, kp = 50u, W = 100u, L = 1u.\n\nAnalyses:\n- Include `.op`.\n- The operating point should show nonzero drain current through M1, M2, M3, M4, M5, M6, M7, M8, and M9.\n- At balanced DC input, Voutp and Vout should settle to similar voltages at real high-impedance gain nodes, preferably near mid-supply with enough headroom for all stacked devices.\n\nOutput constraints:\n- Final netlist filename must be `p21.cir`.\n- The netlist must contain nodes Vinp, Vinn, Vbias1, Vbias2, Vbias3, Vbias4, Voutp, and Vout exactly as named.\n- Every named input node must be driven by an explicit independent voltage source.\n- Do not use subcircuits or hidden placeholder nodes."}}
